comments: Gobert (MIN) establishes himself in Bogdanovic's (ATL) path with his arm slightly extended and marginal body contact occurs as Bogdanovic defends over the pick.
McDaniels (MIN) places his collapsing forearm to Bogdanovic's (ATL) side and marginal contact occurs as McDaniels releases away during the drive.
Bogdanovic (ATL) places his hand to McDaniels' (MIN) side and slides his hand off without applying force as he contests the jump shot attempt.
Gobert (MIN) holds Capela's (ATL) shoulder, which affects his ability to pursue the rebound.
Young (ATL) reaches in and avoids making contact to Gobert's (MIN) arm and body, when Gobert loses control of the ball behind his back.
Bogdanovic (ATL) places his hand to Anderson's (MIN) opposite hip and marginal body contact occurs during his drive to the basket.
Bogdanovic (ATL) makes contact with the ball during Anderson's (MIN) shooting motion and dislodges the ball before incidental arm contact occurs.
Anderson (MIN) and Bogdanovic (ATL) mutually engage and immediately disengage as marginal contact occurs during the rebound.
The shot clock expires before Bogdanovic (ATL) gathers the loose ball.
McDaniels (MIN) briefly places a hand on Collins' (ATL) back and marginal contact occurs, before immediately sliding it off during Collins' driving shot attempt.
Hunter (ATL) briefly places his arm to McDaniels' (MIN) front and marginal contact occurs as the two come together during the screen.
Gobert (MIN) establishes himself in Hunter's (ATL) path and is firming up when contact occurs.
Gobert (MIN) establishes a wide screening position and illegal contact occurs with Young's (ATL) lower body that affects Young's (ATL) ability to defend.
Young (ATL) briefly places his already extended hand to McDaniels' (MIN) front as they come together and marginal contact occurs when he releases away from the contact during his drive.
Capela (ATL) establishes himself in McDaniels' (MIN) path and marginal contact occurs as they disengage.
Capela (ATL) establishes himself in McDaniels's (MIN) path and marginal contact occurs as Capela releases away from the pick.
Gobert (MIN) initiates contact with Young's (ATL) head/face, which affects his driving shot attempt.
Conley (MIN) establishes himself in Young's (ATL) path and is firming up when contact occurs.
Conley (MIN) engages with Young (ATL) off-ball and marginal contact occurs as Conley (MIN) releases away to retrieve the pass.
Towns (MIN) establishes himself in Young's (ATL) path and gives him a step to avoid contact.
Gobert (MIN) is in the lane for less than three seconds when the shot is imminent.
Collins (ATL) contests Towns' (MIN) jump shot and the contact after the release, and follow-through, is marginal.
Bogdanovic (ATL) places his arm to Anderson's (MIN) backside as they come together underneath the basket and marginal contact occurs as they pursue the loose ball.
Bogdanovic (ATL) lifts and replants his pivot foot prior to releasing his dribble.
McDaniels (MIN) moves along Young's (ATL) path and avoids making contact to Young's arm when he briefly loses control of the ball during his gather.
Young (ATL) briefly loses control of the ball during his gather before legally regaining control of it.
Gobert (MIN) is in the paint for less than three seconds when he moves to imminently guard an opponent.
Anderson (MIN) and Hunter (ATL) engage and disengage as marginal contact occurs during the rebound.
Conley (MIN) establishes himself in Collins' (ATL) path and is firming up when contact occurs.

Replay review of the foul called on Collins (ATL) pursuant to a coach's challenge was deemed unsuccessful. Collins (ATL) initiates contact to Towns' (MIN) body, that affects Towns' SQBR during the drive.
Towns (MIN) brings his off-arm toward Collins' (ATL) side and marginal contact occurs as Towns attempts to dribble around Collins  during the drive.
McDaniels (MIN) and Young (ATL) engage and disengage with one another and marginal contact occurs off-ball.
Bey (ATL) briefly grasps Prince's (MIN) arm off ball and immediately slides his arm off as they separate.
Collins (ATL) engages with Gobert (MIN) off-ball and marginal contact occurs as Collins releases away to retrieve the pass.
Gobert (MIN) contests Hunter's (ATL) jump shot and the contact after the release, and follow-through, is marginal.
Prince (MIN) moves backwards into Bey's (ATL) body and the contact affects his put-back shot attempt at the basket.
